#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

# SessionStart hook — reminds Claude about available optimus skills on every
# session start, resume, clear, and compact. Keeps the catalog minimal to
# reduce token overhead.

cat <<'CATALOG'
## Optimus Skills Available

Check if any of these skills apply before responding:

| Skill | Use when... |
|-------|-------------|
| `/optimus:init` | Setting up a project for Claude Code (CLAUDE.md, docs, hooks, agents) |
| `/optimus:tdd` | Implementing a feature or bug fix test-first (Red-Green-Refactor) |
| `/optimus:unit-test` | Improving unit test coverage for existing code |
| `/optimus:code-review` | Reviewing local changes, branch diffs, or PRs/MRs |
| `/optimus:simplify` | Cleaning up code quality drift (duplication, pattern inconsistency) |
| `/optimus:commit-message` | Generating a conventional commit message from staged changes |
| `/optimus:permissions` | Configuring Claude Code permissions for safe autonomy |

If the user's task matches a skill, suggest it (e.g., "You might want to run `/optimus:tdd` for this"). These skills require explicit user invocation — do not attempt to call them programmatically.
CATALOG
